title: Lanett Municipal Airport
text:
Lanett Municipal Airport is a city-owned public-use <a href="airport">airport</a> located three nautical miles (6 km) southwest of the <a href="central%20business%20district">central business district</a> of <a href="Lanett%2C%20Alabama">Lanett</a>, a city in <a href="Chambers%20County%2C%20Alabama">Chambers County</a>, <a href="Alabama">Alabama</a>, <a href="United%20States">United States</a>. According to the FAA's <a href="National%20Plan%20of%20Integrated%20Airport%20Systems">National Plan of Integrated Airport Systems</a> for 2009–2013, it is <a href="FAA%20airport%20categories">categorized</a> as a "<a href="general%20aviation">general aviation</a>" facility.
Facilities and aircraft.
Lanett Municipal Airport covers an area of at an <a href="elevation">elevation</a> of 624 feet (190 m) above <a href="mean%20sea%20level">mean sea level</a>. It has one <a href="runway">runway</a> designated 8/26 with an <a href="asphalt">asphalt</a> surface measuring 3,148 by 80 feet (960 x 24 m).
For the 12-month period ending February 24, 2010, the airport had 3,290 aircraft operations, an average of 274 per month: 99.7% <a href="general%20aviation">general aviation</a> and 0.3% <a href="military%20aviation">military</a>.
At that time there were 13 aircraft based at this airport: 84.6% single-<a href="aircraft%20engine">engine</a>, 7.7% multi-engine and 7.7% <a href="ultralight">ultralight</a>.
